Peter M. Gotsch  Managing Director, Svoboda Capital Partners LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships52--
Background

		Mr. Peter M. Gotsch serves as Managing Director at Svoboda Capital Partners LLC. Mr. Gotsch joined Svoboda Capital Partners LLC in 2011. He has over 20 years of experience in the private equity industry. He served as the Managing Partner at Ellipse Capital LLC. He was a Partner with CHS Capital, Code. He served as a Co-Head of the Distribution Team at CHS Capital. He was Investment Professional at First Chicago Corporation. He served as the Chairman of Houston Wire & ... Cable Company until November 2007. He serves on the boards of Advanced Applied Adhesives, Inc., GPA Holdings, Reliable Parts Ltd., Blake & Pendleton, Inc, Grabber Construction Products, Inc., Monroe Engineering Products, Inc., Applied Adhesives and Ward Adhesives. He has been a Director of Triad Technologies, LLC and Berkline/BenchCraft Holdings LLC since 2002. He serves as a Director of Houston Wire & Cable Company. He also serves on the Board of Regents for St. Olaf College. He is a Member of the Northshore Concert Band. Mr. Gotsch served as a Director of Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. from 1997 to February 10, 2017 and its Lead Director from January 01, 2011 to February 10, 2017. He served as a Director of Houston Wire & Cable Company since 1997 until May 6, 2014. He served as a Director of Pool Corporation and The Hillman Companies from March 31, 2004 to June 2010. Mr. Gotsch holds an M.B.A. from the Kellogg Graduate School of Business at Northwestern University and a B.A. degree with honors from St. Olaf College.Read Full Background




